g.text: Substitutional doping confirmation for the Al going in Si site for Mg2Si
GGA-WC XC Functional calculated total energies of doped Mg2Si

•XRD patterns showing clean single-phase patterns for all samples.•Crystal structures of Mg2SixAlyremains anti-fluorite cubic with y increase but lattice parameter increases in ranging from 6.351 for y=0 to 6.367 Å for y=0.03, indicating that partial Si sites were occupied by Al3+ions because ral=118pm > rsi=111pm.•From Raman Spectra, 2 strong absorption peaks located at ν3 ≈ 257cm-1 and ν4 ≈ 347 cm-1 may be attributed to the internal phonon modes; stretching ν3and bending ν4.•Raman Peak Shift in LO and TO is a result of distortion in the lattice, making it more asymetericalas y increases. With increasing y, first intensity decreases then increases intensity and shifts towards lower frequency. LO and TO mode shift to lower frequency can be of 2 vibrations: (i) Mg-Si stretching vibration (ii) Mg-Al stretching in Mg2Si tetrahedral.
